So the pi-subagents extension could hook into this event to get the skill paths from pi's settings instead of hardcoding them. Let me look at how pi's settings work to see if there's a way to access them.

Actually, looking at the skills.md doc more carefully:
> Pi loads skills from:
> - Global: `~/.pi/agent/skills/`
> - Project: `.pi/skills/`
> - Packages: `skills/` directories or `pi.skills` entries in `package.json`
> - Settings: `skills` array with files or directories

So pi itself reads from a `skills` setting. The subagents extension should ideally use the same discovery mechanism or at least respect the same settings.

